Words for Amount or Form

Some words describe the amount or shape of something.

a loaf of bread
a ball of string
a bar of soap
a bar of chocolate


A Piece Of

The phrase a piece of means a single serving or a single part of something.

a slice or piece of bread
a piece or square of chocolate
a sheet or piece of paper
a piece of information
a slice or piece of cheese
a slice or piece of cake
a piece of chalk
a piece of advice
